title: Sequence of Subbarrier Fission Resonances in 236U

x4freetext: The State University of New York at
Stony Brook model FN tandem Van de Graaff.
Targets consisted of 60-microg/cm2 isotopic 235U02
evaporated onto 40-microg/cm2 carbon foils. A
4.65-mg/cm2 Al foil in front of the dE-E telescope
eliminated fission fragments.
Coincident pairs of fission fragments
were detected at +-90 degrees with respect to the
beam axis in two thin-film plastic scintillator
detectors each of which subtended a solid angle of
1.25 sr. Outgoing protons were detected in a dE-E
telescope placed out of the beam-fission-detector
plane at 60 and 140 degrees. The solid angle of the
telescope was 19.9 msr. Differential (d,pf) cross
sections were obtained from energy spectra of protons
in coincidence with fission,  assuming an isotropic
proton-fission correlation. The energy calibration (+-
30 keV) was obtained from elastic deuteron scattering.
Differential cross sections were corrected for small
accidental contributions.

resonance region was subtracted from the data. When
these smooth curves are subtracted from the fission
cross sections, a set of resonances is clearly and
consistently revealed.
